.TH "drm_dp_mst_atomic_check" 9 "drm_dp_mst_atomic_check" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dp_mst_atomic_check \- Check that the new state of an MST topology in an atomic update is valid
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_dp_mst_atomic_check
.BI "(struct drm_atomic_state *state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
Pointer to the new \fIstruct drm_dp_mst_topology_state\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks the given topology state for an atomic update to ensure that it's
valid. This includes checking whether there's enough bandwidth to support
the new VCPI allocations in the atomic update.

Any atomic drivers supporting DP MST must make sure to call this after
checking the rest of their state in their
\fIdrm_mode_config_funcs\fP.\fBatomic_check\fP callback.

See also:
\fBdrm_dp_atomic_find_vcpi_slots\fP
\fBdrm_dp_atomic_release_vcpi_slots\fP

0 if the new state is valid, negative error code otherwise.
.SH "RETURN"
